            "debriefing": {
                "title": "Thank you!",
                "blocks": [
                    {
                        "text": "Debrief",
                        "listblocks": [
                            {
                                "text": "In this activity, your child heard about characters doing some activities. We asked whether your child thought each character's parent would step in and complete a task for their child. We also asked you (the parent or legal guardian) about whether you would step in and complete the same tasks for your child if they were struggling. In these questions there were no right or wrong answers! Broadly, we are interested in whether children expect parents to step in (e.g., because they know parents are kind and helpful) or step back (e.g., because they know parents want their children to learn to do the tasks on their own). We are also curious about whether children's predictions about the characters in the study will relate to what their own parent reported here. For example, does your child expect a character's parent to finish a puzzle if you (the parent or legal guardian) indicated that you would help your child finish a puzzle?" 
                                },
                            {
                                "text": "Critically, as mentioned above, there were no right or wrong answers to the questions in the parent survey or in the child-directed portion of the study. We are so grateful for your participation, which will help us learn a great deal more about how children think about the role of parents in their success. You can find more of our lab's work at <a href='https://learninglab.yale.edu/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>on our website</a>. If you'd like to learn more about how children understand parenting, check out <a href='https://drive.google.com/file/d/1emDLQ0DVPJE8uYXP6h4uRV4NdKkZctdM/view?usp=sharing' target='_blank' rel='noopener'> this article</a>! If you'd like to learn more about overparenting, check out <a href='https://jlnrd.github.io/Publications/Leonard%20et%20al.,%202021.pdf' target='_blank' rel='noopener'> this article</a>!"
                            }
